
“I felt SAD because I saw the others were SAD and because I knew I should feel SAD, but I wasn’t really SAD.”
Roberto Bolano, 2666

Examples of Sentence RepetitionFour repetitions of the word “SAD”.
But every time the word is functioning in different ways.

He feels SAD.
Others feel SAD
He is being forced into happiness (is he actually SAD?)
The truth: He is actually not SAD at all
